Description: Clay figure made of a fine brown Nile clay that was consolidated with a glossy substance after excavation. The object is oval with a flat base and well rounded ends. One of the ends is broken off just after the end turns upwards. A cylindrical hole runs horizontally through the middle section with a diameter of 0.5 cm. A very small pierced hole on the upper part (closest to the pinched section) can also be seen, not sure if this is intentionally. Clay figurine with additional pieces attached like a bird?
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), D14.16B, upper layer
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 148)
